longBusinessSummary: Fox River Resources Corporation engages in acquiring, exploring, evaluating, and developing mineral and natural resources properties. Its primary asset is the Martison phosphate project with mining leases and claims covering a contiguous area of approximately 8,256 hectares located in north-central Ontario. The company was incorporated in 2015 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
